This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image compression. The use of recurrent convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses code compression, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for image compression could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
